Graduations log (meta-log, `memory_type: meta-log`) appears here when first graduation fires: `graduations.md`.

## How to use

- **Before starting a new design task** — check `lessons/<domain>.md` for prior episodes on the topic
- **Before shipping a significant change** — check `decisions.md` to see what's already chosen and why
- **After completing work** — capture via `/hd:maintain capture`; lesson appends to the relevant `lessons/<domain>.md`
- **When a pattern recurs 3+ times** — run `/hd:maintain graduate-propose <topic>`; rule lands in `AGENTS.md`, meta-entry in `graduations.md`

## Split threshold

When any single file exceeds ~15 entries, propose splitting by sub-domain. Example: `lessons/integration.md` (20 entries) → `lessons/integration-notion.md` + `lessons/integration-figma.md`. `/hd:maintain capture` surfaces the split when triggered.

